  "prompt": "I'm a MBBS student in India. I would like to do my medical PG in Australia. What should I do for the same?",
  "response": "To pursue a medical postgraduate (PG) degree in Australia as an Indian MBBS graduate, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Requirements:\n- Complete MBBS degree from a recognized medical college\n- Clear the screening test by the Australian Medical Council (AMC)\n- Demonstrate English language proficiency (IELTS/OET)\n\n2. AMC Certification Process:\n- Register for AMC examination\n- Clear AMC Multiple Choice Question (MCQ) exam\n- Clear AMC Clinical exam\n- Obtain AMC certification\n\n3. Registration Requirements:\n- Apply to Medical Board of Australia\n- Provide all necessary documentation\n- Get provisional registration\n\n4. Pathway Options:\n- Standard training pathway\n- Specialist training programs\n- International medical graduate programs\n\n5. Examination Preparations:\n- IELTS/OET preparation\n- AMC exam preparation\n- Clinical skills enhancement\n\n6. Additional Recommendations:\n- Research specific specialty requirements\n- Understand visa regulations\n- Consider financial planning\n- Network with Australian medical professionals\n\n7. Recommended Platforms:\n- Australian Medical Council website\n- Medical Board of Australia website\n- Australian Healthcare recruitment portals\n\nConsult with educational consultants specializing in medical migrations for personalized guidance.",
